The paper discusses privacy preservation in mobile location-based services, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a metric to quantify privacy exposure, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data, making it relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper addresses privacy concerns related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and mobile computing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of privacy-preserving solutions on user behavior, which is related to the sub-category of computers and society (cs.CY).
